<section>
    <div class="page-header">
        <h2 id="icons">Icons</h2>
    </div>

    <p>BraincraftedBootstrapBundle provides a function to include Glyphicons in templates.</p>

    <pre><code class="twig">{{ "&lt;button type=&quot;button&quot; class=&quot;btn btn-default btn-lg&quot;&gt;{{ icon('camera') }} Camera&lt;/button&gt;" }}</code></pre>

    <div class="panel">
        <div class="panel-body disable-links">
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-lg">{{ icon('camera') }} Camera</button>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-footer">Button with icon</div>
    </div>

    <p>There is also a filter to parse icons in a string of text. Just use <code>.icon-NAME</code> anywhere in the string and the filter will replace it with the HTML code.</p>

    <pre><code class="twig">{{ "{{ 'This is the story of a .icon-paperclip that travled the .icon-globe with his .icon-headphones on.'|parse_icons }}" }}</code></pre>

    <div class="panel">
        <div class="panel-body disable-links">
            {{ 'This is the story of a .icon-paperclip that travled the .icon-globe with his .icon-headphones on.'|parse_icons }}
        </div>
        <div class="panel-footer">Icons defined inside a string</div>
    </div>

    <p>{{ label_info('Info') }} You need to install the Glyphicon icon font before this will work. More information are in the <a href="{{ path('braincrafted_bootstrap_getting_started') }}#installing-glyphicons">installation instructions</a>.</p>

    <p>{{ label_info('Info') }} You can use a different icon set with BootstrapBundle. Include the other icon set in your stylesheets and change the value of <code>braincrafted_bootstrap.icon_prefix</code> to the appropriate prefix.</p>

    <h3>Font Awesome</h3>

    <p>BootstrapBundle works with Font Awesome. First you need to add Font Awesome to your project. For example, you can use Composer and add the official package to your <code>composer.json</code>:</p>

    <pre><code class="shell">$ composer require fortawesome/font-awesome:~4.0</code></pre>

    <p>Next you need to change the icon prefix to <code>fa</code>:</p>

    <pre><code class="yaml">braincrafted_bootstrap:
  icon_prefix: fa</code></pre>

    <p>{{ label_info('Info') }} If you used another method to install Font Awesome (e.g., Bower or direct download) you probably need to change the <code>braincrafted_bootstrap.fontawesome_dir</code> option to point to the directory where the Font Awesome files are located.</p>


</section>
